conflicts: none
open gaps: drift-guard
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED or NotFound are
delete-confirmation targets.
Existing-before-create lookup runs only when
both dashboardGroupId and displayName are
present, then scopes ListDashboards by exact
dashboardGroupId plus displayName and reuses
only a unique candidate in ACTIVE, CREATING, or
UPDATING.
The published runtime dispatches polymorphic
create and update bodies by schemaVersion,
currently supports only V1, defaults an omitted
schemaVersion to V1, and rejects unsupported
schema versions before OCI mutation.
Only displayName, description, freeformTags,
definedTags, config, and widgets reconcile in
place. dashboardGroupId moves via
ChangeDashboardGroup remain out of scope, and
schemaVersion plus systemTags remain
replacement-only drift. Empty-string displayName
or description values and null config values are
treated as omission until the spec can
distinguish clear from omit.
Create, get, and update return the Dashboard
body polymorphically, list returns
DashboardSummary items only, delete returns
headers only, and the Dashboards home-region
caveat remains explicit in the published runtime
contract.
end note
